{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d98484f5-7178-437f-ad73-f0b0e1ef375d","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with **MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0**, the change is straightforward:\n\n**Remove** the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property from your project file (`.csproj`).\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n\n<!-- After -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key things to know:**\n\n1. **MSTest.Sdk defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform** — `UseVSTest` was the opt-out. Removing it switches you over.\n2. **Run tests differently** — use `dotnet test` as before, but you can also run the test project directly (`dotnet run`) since it now produces an executable.\n3. **CLI differences** — some VSTest CLI options (e.g., `--filter`) still work, but the native form is `--filter` → `--treenode-filter`. Check `dotnet test -- --help` for platform-specific options.\n4. **Remove any VSTest-specific packages** — if you manually referenced `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`, it's no longer needed (MSTest.Sdk handles dependencies).\n5. **Runsettings** — `.runsettings` files are still supported but some adapter-specific settings may need adjustment.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c0eee0fe-8f4a-4924-92d9-ff54a8e0cec2","outputTokens":415,"requestId":"6804:397CAF:72C1C6:7A03A7:6A044D50"},"id":"2f617be6-ec6c-4922-a6a6-49ce79019816","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:23.878Z","parentId":"821ee956-c63c-4023-8631-7ba782f4d5c7"}
